- **Classifier Development**: Fine-tuning RoBERTa and comparing it with baseline models (e.g., BERT, DeBERTa, PoliBERT) in identifying stance shifts between sources and summaries.
- **Bias Attribution Analysis**: Using interpretability methods (e.g., attention, LIME, integrated gradients) to examine whether the model detects surface-level cues or deeper structural biases.

The project seeks to advance fairness in AI-generated content by enabling better auditing of summarization systems and informing future debiasing techniques, with implications for algorithmic transparency under regulatory frameworks like the EU AI Act.
